{
  "stem": "10862.3",
  "chunk_idx": 15,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And then we kept walking and walking and walking till finally we reached Demblin.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And Demblin was the city where we had the camp for two years.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "That's the same place.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And, of course, when we got there January 1945, there was nobody there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Nobody had survived.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And we were there for a little bit, for a little while.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we were hoping that we would find-- our father we knew was dead because our father had been killed right away.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were hoping that maybe my mother or my sister, aunts and uncles, somebody could have survived.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were hoping that we would find somebody because we sort of had a central point that we said if anybody survives, we're going back to there.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We knew that there was nothing in Warsaw because Warsaw was destroyed during the uprising of April 1943 when they had the uprising.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we knew Warsaw was not left anymore to go back to.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And Demblin was a small town.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We thought we will go back there thinking that maybe my aunts and uncles had survived.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But when we came there, there was nothing there, and the Polish people were not very nice.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They just were not nice.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They did not treat us very nicely.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We found a bombed-out house without a roof and whoever was there, the people that came, you know, gathered just like we did, we stayed in that house.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was the bitter cold, bitter winter.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "No food.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The Russian even had less food than the Germans.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They had nothing, the Russians.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I used to go to the garbage looking for food, and most of the time I would find like potato peelings.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
